  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">NIHR Global Health Research Group on Social Policy and Health Inequalities</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">1) Expand the research potential of the 100M cohort by adding further data: geographical information including an indicator of the deprivation of each person&#x2019;s area of residence (created as part of this project) and data on non-communicable diseases from hospitals and other sources. 2) Evaluate the impact of specific policies (a welfare programme and a subsidised housing programme) on health and health inequalities. 3) Measure Brazil&#x2019;s progress against the Sustainable Development Goals on non-communicable diseases for different social groups. 4) Build research capacity in the evaluation of public health programmes internationally through the development and delivery of a course. 5) Develop and maintain a strong relationship with stakeholders, including policy makers and practitioners, so that analyses and results are focused, useful, timely and accessible. This will maximise the opportunity for action to be taken as a result of this research and will lead to the joint production of future research.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">A UK and low- and middle-income country (LMIC) partnership that aims to improve population health by studying the social determinants of health and to further understanding of how social policy may reduce health inequalities globally.</narrative>
  </description>
